LASSA FEVER - WEST AFRICA (17): NIGERIA
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 12 Dec 2021
Source: Nigeria Center for Disease Control (NCDC) [edited]
https://bit.ly/2KTJfrL


Key points
----------
Current week (49): 6-12 Dec 2021 / Cumulative 2021 weeks 1-49 / Cumulative 2020 weeks 1-49
- Suspected cases: 123 / 4083 / 6535
- Confirmed cases: 10 / 444 / 1158
- Probable cases: 1 / 5 / 14
- Deaths: 3 / 83 / 240
- Case fatality rate (CFR [%]): 30 / 18.7 / 20.7
- Number of states affected: 3 / 16 / 27
- Local government areas (LGAs) affected: 6 / 64 / 130

Highlights
----------
- In week 49, the number of new confirmed cases increased from 4 in week 48 2021 to 10 cases. These were reported from Ondo, Edo and Nasarawa States (Table 3)
- Cumulatively from week 1 to week 49 2021, 83 deaths have been reported with a case fatality rate (CFR) of 18.7% which is lower than the CFR for the same period in 2020 (20.7%)
- In total for 2021, 16 States have recorded at least one confirmed case across 64 Local Government Areas (Figure 2 and 3)
- Of all confirmed cases, 84% are from Edo (44%), Ondo (35%) and Taraba( 5%) States.
- The predominant age-group affected is 21-30 years (range: <1 to 70years, median age:29 years). The male to female ratio for confirmed cases is 1:0.8 (Figure4)
- The number of suspected cases has decreased compared to that reported for the same period in 2020
- Two new health care workers affected in the reporting week 49
- National Lassa fever multi-partner, multi-sectoral Technical Working Group (TWG) continues to coordinate the response activities at all levels

